      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Model routing is the practice of directing each task or sub-task in an agent pipeline to the model tier best suited for it \u2014 balancing cost, latency, and quality across the run. Rather than calling the most capable (and most expensive) model for every step, a router classifies each task and selects the appropriate tier. Applied correctly, routing can reduce total token cost by 50\u201380% on mixed-workload pipelines without measurable quality loss."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Model routing \u2014 tasks classified and directed to Haiku, Sonnet, or Opus"
        }
