          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Route?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A typical coding agent run involves many different step types: reading files, classifying output, planning refactors, writing code, running tests, summarising results. These steps vary widely in difficulty. Routing each to the appropriate model tier turns the cost profile from flat (every step at Opus price) to proportional (cheap steps are cheap, hard steps get the power they need):"
          }
        ]
