          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Model routing reduces agent pipeline costs by directing each task to the cheapest model capable of handling it well. A keyword router is the simplest implementation: scan for simple/hard signals, default to the balanced tier. A meta-router that uses Haiku to classify tasks achieves more reliable routing at the cost of one extra cheap API call per task. Wrap routing logic in a stateful class that tracks tier usage and supports dry-run mode for testing. Apply routing at the per-step level inside agent loops to capture savings on the mechanical execution steps that make up the majority of most runs."
